name: Gogetsale
tag_list: social-commerce, facebook-app, start-up, shopping, e-commerce, social-media
description: The next generation of online shopping.
overview:
What is GoGetSale? GoGetSale is the next generation of online shopping. Harnessing the power of social media, GoGetSale allows members of these networks to join the GoGetSale community, to invite their friends join and earn money from every purchase, they and the friends in their networks make.

GoGetSale redistributes 80% of the gross commissions it receives from suppliers and retailers to its members, at a percentage determined by their position in the GoGetSale structure. The more friends you have making purchases, the more money you make.

Members can choose to have their earnings credited through their UK bank accounts or their PayPal account. Members receive the money they have earned on a monthly basis. Payments are made when members have earned £10 to reduce the costs of making multiple transfers.

In addition, GoGetSale offers unparalleled benefits to retailers as it takes online marketing to a more targeted level than ever before. As purchases are made, the retailers’ products spread organically throughout the GoGetSale community, reaching the members most likely to be interested in making a purchase. It is possible to buy from over 800 retailers and millions of products using GoGetSale.

Sequoia Tree Sequoia trees are amongst the oldest trees in the world. GoGetSale members are allocated a membership level below the level of the member who invited them to become a member. There are four membership levels as follows: (a) Trunk, (b) Branch, (c) Twig, (d) Leaf. For example, if a Trunk invites you to become a member, you become a Branch. If a Branch invites you to become a member, you become a Twig and if a Twig invites you, to become a member you become a Leaf. Charity Partners GoGetSale has the following charity partners: NODA
